{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NY6UEzkR4YvEPdiDh1qhCx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 4)\n     2→\n     3→### 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode — code-review (2026-03-20T06:50Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **HIGH: Command injection** — `execSync(cfg.testCommand)` executed unsanitized user input. Fixed with metacharacter rejection.\n     6→- **HIGH: Query timeout too short** — 3s health timeout reused for queries. Fixed with 30s query-specific timeout.\n     7→- **MEDIUM: Malformed URL crash** — `new URL()` in `queryTelemetryEvents` could throw. Fixed with try/catch.\n     8→- **LOW (not fixed): File grew to 212 lines** — story target was 200. Justified by security hardening.\n     9→- **LOW (not fixed): `parseLogEvents` silently drops malformed JSON** — no counter or warning.\n    10→- **LOW (not fixed): Substring module matching** — `event.source.includes(mod)` can false-positive on short names.\n    11→- **Architecture: `saveRuntimeCoverage` doesn't persist module details** — Story 3.1 must address.\n    12→\n    13→### 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode — dev-story (2026-03-20T06:43Z)\n    14→\n    15→- **Task 3 persistence gap:** `validateRuntime()` returns `RuntimeValidationResult` but `saveRuntimeCoverage()` doesn't persist the `modules` array — only aggregate stats. Story 3.1 (audit coordinator) will need to extend persistence.\n    16→- **Branch coverage at 76%:** Statement/function/line coverage is 100% but defensive fallbacks in ndjson parsing have uncovered branches.\n    17→- **File size at limit:** `runtime-validator.ts` is exactly 200 lines — the story's cap. Any future additions need care.\n    18→\n    19→### 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode — create-story (2026-03-20T06:36Z)\n    20→\n    21→- **Ambiguity: epic-2 status.** Sprint-status.yaml shows `epic-2: backlog` despite stories 2-1 and 2-2 being `done`. Left as-is per instructions.\n    22→- **No audit CLI command exists yet.** Epic 3 / Story 3.1 creates `codeharness audit`. This story implements the module function only (`validateRuntime()`), not a CLI surface.\n    23→- **Risk: AC 1 is hard to verify in isolation.** Requires running VictoriaLogs, OTLP-instrumented test suite, and test execution producing telemetry. Tagged as integration-required.\n    24→- **Risk: Module detection heuristic.** Architecture says \"module-level matching\" for runtime coverage but doesn't specify how to discover modules or map telemetry events to them.\n    25→- **Workaround: No config.yaml at expected `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`** — actual path is `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n    26→\n    27→---\n    28→\n    29→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 3)\n    30→\n    31→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story AC3 fix (2026-03-20T06:18Z)\n    32→\n    33→- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` for coverage numbers and once via `readCachedGaps()` for gap data. `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include gaps field — adding it would cascade. Acceptable for now.\n    34→- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead.\n    35→- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by older version without gaps field, gate returns empty gaps. Graceful degradation but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run.\n    36→\n    37→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:28Z)\n    38→\n    39→- **All 3 ACs PASS** — black-box verification confirmed gap data flows end-to-end.\n    40→- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — codeharness CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected — it instruments other projects, not itself).\n    41→- **pre-commit-gate.sh not in npm dist** — hook is a Claude Code plugin artifact, not packaged in npm tarball. Verifier correctly noted this and tested via the CLI command instead.\n    42→- **Stale container from prior session** — had to `docker rm -f` before starting. verify-env cleanup should handle this.\n    43→\n    44→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:25Z)\n    45→\n    46→- **HIGH: Double file read in coverage-gate.ts** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` read sprint-state.json twice independently (once for coverage, once for gaps). Fixed by adding gaps to StaticCoverageState and parsing in extractCoverageState().\n    47→- **HIGH: Gaps never parsed back through readCoverageState** — StaticCoverageState lacked gaps field, so AC 3 always showed empty. Root cause of the verify failure. Fixed.\n    48→- **MEDIUM: Fix suggestion referenced generic patches/ path** — changed to reference actual codeharness observability-gate command.\n    49→- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated default target constants** in coverage.ts and coverage-gate.ts.\n    50→- **LOW (not fixed): No integration test for full gap flow** (write state → run gate → verify gaps appear).\n    51→\n    52→---\n    53→\n    54→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 2)\n    55→\n    56→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify (2026-03-20T06:10Z)\n    57→\n    58→- **AC 3 FAIL: `gapSummary` hardcoded as empty array** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` never reads gap data from sprint-state.json or calls analyzer. The formatting code exists but has no data to display.\n    59→- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command** — block message references it but command doesn't exist.\n    60→- **AC 1 and AC 2 PASS** — basic gate behavior works correctly.\n    61→- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected for a tool that instruments other projects).\n    62→- Returning to dev for AC 3 fix.\n    63→\n    64→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review (2026-03-20T06:15Z)\n    65→\n    66→- **HIGH: `saveCoverageResult` dropped `runtime` field** — every `codeharness analyze` run wiped runtime coverage data from sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n    67→- **HIGH: No NaN validation on `--min-static`/`--min-runtime`** — `parseInt` with non-numeric input silently set NaN target, gate always failed with no error. Fixed.\n    68→- **HIGH: `timeout` command not on stock macOS** — observability gate check silently never ran on Mac. Fixed by removing `timeout`.\n    69→- **MEDIUM: AGENTS.md files not updated** — coverage-gate.ts and observability-gate.ts missing from module docs. Fixed.\n    70→- **LOW (not fixed): Grep-based JSON parsing in pre-commit-gate.sh** — fragile, pre-existing pattern.\n    71→- **LOW (not fixed): Unreachable DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET fallback** — dead defensive code.\n    72→\n    73→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story (2026-03-20T06:00Z)\n    74→\n    75→- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** 4 tests in `tests/integration/hooks.bats` (tests 28-31) fail on master — `hooks.json` format mismatch. Not caused by this story.\n    76→- **`extractCoverageState` was incomplete:** Existing function didn't parse `runtime` section or `runtimeTarget` from sprint-state.json, even though Story 2.1 writes runtime data. Extended it — technically a bug fix for Story 2.1.\n    77→- **Gap details limited in hook:** Hook directs users to run `codeharness analyze` instead of showing file/line details (Semgrep too slow for hook context).\n    78→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n    79→\n    80→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — create-story (2026-03-20T05:50Z)\n    81→\n    82→- **Ambiguity in AC 3:** Epic says block message should include specific files/functions missing logging. Getting specific gaps requires running Semgrep (~10s), violating 500ms hook NFR. Story resolves by using cached coverage and directing user to `codeharness analyze`.\n    83→- **Risk: `coverage.ts` line limit.** Existing file is 269 lines; adding gate function (~40 lines) may exceed 300-line NFR9 limit.\n    84→- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command exists yet.** Story references it in error messages but no such subcommand exists. Dev needs to create it or adjust messaging.\n    85→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n    86→\n    87→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-19T09:00Z)\n    88→\n    89→- **Epic 0.5 appeared:** The create-story agent added a new Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) to sprint-status.yaml despite being told not to modify it. This is a workflow compliance issue.\n    90→- **AC #1 integration risk:** Verifying that the verifier queries observability after docker exec requires a live verification session — hard to test in isolation.\n    91→- **Tag coupling risk:** `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format is a convention between prompt template and parser regex. If verifier (Claude) doesn't emit exact format, parser won't detect it.\n    92→- **Naming confusion:** Epic 2 retrospective file references a different Epic 2 from a previous sprint.\n    93→\n    94→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-19T09:08Z)\n    95→\n    96→- **Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\n    97→- **logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\n    98→- **VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\n    99→- **Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\n   100→\n   101→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-19T09:15Z)\n   102→\n   103→- **HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n   104→- **MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\n   105→- **MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\n   106→- **LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\n   107→- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\n   108→- **LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\n   109→- **Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\n   110→- **Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\n   111→\n   112→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — verify (2026-03-20T05:40Z)\n   113→\n   114→- **Proof markdown parsing bug:** Verifier embedded a heredoc containing nested code fences (````bash`/````output`) inside a bash code block. The closing backticks broke out of the outer fence, causing `## AC N: PASS` headings from the test proof to appear as real AC sections. The proof parser counted 8 ACs instead of 4. Fixed by summarizing the heredoc content.\n   115→- **Evidence adjacency requirement:** The proof parser requires `bash` and `output` code blocks to be adjacent (no text between them). AC3 had explanatory text between the blocks, causing it to be counted as pending. Fixed by removing the intervening text.\n   116→- **VictoriaLogs zero events:** The codeharness CLI does not emit OpenTelemetry data in the Docker container, so all observability gap checks return empty. This is expected for a tool that instruments other projects, not itself.\n   117→- **AC1 template verification limitation:** The verify-prompt.ts template compiles into the Claude Code plugin (skills/), not the npm CLI binary. Cannot directly inspect the template from Docker. Verified via the template-to-parser contract (OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG constant, parseObservabilityGaps function, verify --json output fields).\n   118→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea9dcd26-048d-426f-9aa1-49ae9968ed9a","uuid":"2c970581-f0d0-4ac1-95a9-e10244274ee2","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:49:42.687Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 4)\n\n### 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode — code-review (2026-03-20T06:50Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Command injection** — `execSync(cfg.testCommand)` executed unsanitized user input. Fixed with metacharacter rejection.\n- **HIGH: Query timeout too short** — 3s health timeout reused for queries. Fixed with 30s query-specific timeout.\n- **MEDIUM: Malformed URL crash** — `new URL()` in `queryTelemetryEvents` could throw. Fixed with try/catch.\n- **LOW (not fixed): File grew to 212 lines** — story target was 200. Justified by security hardening.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `parseLogEvents` silently drops malformed JSON** — no counter or warning.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Substring module matching** — `event.source.includes(mod)` can false-positive on short names.\n- **Architecture: `saveRuntimeCoverage` doesn't persist module details** — Story 3.1 must address.\n\n### 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode — dev-story (2026-03-20T06:43Z)\n\n- **Task 3 persistence gap:** `validateRuntime()` returns `RuntimeValidationResult` but `saveRuntimeCoverage()` doesn't persist the `modules` array — only aggregate stats. Story 3.1 (audit coordinator) will need to extend persistence.\n- **Branch coverage at 76%:** Statement/function/line coverage is 100% but defensive fallbacks in ndjson parsing have uncovered branches.\n- **File size at limit:** `runtime-validator.ts` is exactly 200 lines — the story's cap. Any future additions 