{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011SHxi28VChqCatb4SAyHZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014MGnHj9uN3YHZ3TVHF3SVz","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. The story is about a standalone runtime check function (validateRuntime) for audit mode. Here are the 3 ACs:\n\n1. Given codeharness audit runs, When OTLP is enabled and tests run, Then the observability backend is queried for telemetry events during the test window.\n2. Given 8 modules in the project and 5 emitted telemetry, When reported, Then runtime coverage = 62.5% with the 3 silent modules listed.\n3. Given the observability stack is not running, When the runtime check runs, Then it reports 'runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available' as a warning, not a hard failure.\n\nKEY CONTEXT: This story implements a MODULE-LEVEL FUNCTION (validateRuntime), NOT a CLI command. The codeharness audit CLI command does NOT exist yet (that is Story 3.1). To verify these ACs, you must call the exported functions directly via node -e inside the Docker container. The observability module is installed at /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js and exports: validateRuntime, checkBackendHealth, queryTelemetryEvents, mapEventsToModules.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n- The container has: codeharness CLI, node, npm, curl, jq\n\n### How to call the functions\n\nUse docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \\\"...\\\" to call the exported functions. Examples:\n\nFor AC1 (validateRuntime queries backend):\n- Create a temp dir, call validateRuntime with a test config pointing at the real observability backend. It should run the test command, query the backend, and return results.\n- The observability backend (VictoriaLogs) is accessible at http://localhost:9428 from inside the container (--network host).\n\nFor AC2 (coverage computation):\n- Call mapEventsToModules with mock data representing 8 modules where 5 have telemetry. Verify coverage = 62.5% and the 3 silent modules are listed.\n- Or call validateRuntime on a project with known modules and verify the math.\n\nFor AC3 (graceful skip when stack down):\n- Call validateRuntime with a queryEndpoint pointing to a non-existent host (e.g. http://localhost:99999). It should return a skipped result with reason containing 'runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available'.\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- VictoriaLogs (logs): http://localhost:9428\n- VictoriaMetrics (metrics): http://localhost:8428\n\n## Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\n\nAfter EACH docker exec command you run, query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds:\n\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n\nIf the response contains one or more log entries, note the count. If zero, include: [OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n## AC N: description\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.** Never use bare fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. ALL commands MUST use docker exec codeharness-verify ... — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. Do NOT attempt to access source code — there is no src/ directory in this workspace.\n3. Report REAL failures — if a feature does not work, report that as a verification failure with specific details. Do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. Every AC needs functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence.\n5. [ESCALATE] is ONLY for things that are genuinely impossible to automate — physical hardware, paid external services, human visual judgment. Infrastructure problems are NOT valid escalation reasons.\n6. Never switch to unit-testable verification. If Docker verification does not work, report WHY as a [FAIL].\" 2>&1","description":"Run verifier session for story 2-3","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":244,"cache_read_input_tokens":55728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":244},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea9dcd26-048d-426f-9aa1-49ae9968ed9a","uuid":"b5c59004-1ebd-4622-9e5c-52381dc77eb9"}
