{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XRAnxnn9c4cePu8cHuuNRS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 2.3: Standalone Runtime Check (Audit Mode) — Verification Proof\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-20\n     4→**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n     5→**Container:** codeharness-verify\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## AC 1: Given codeharness audit runs, When OTLP is enabled and tests run, Then the observability backend is queried for telemetry events during the test window\n    10→\n    11→**Verdict: FAIL**\n    12→\n    13→### Evidence\n    14→\n    15→First, confirm the 4 exported functions exist:\n    16→\n    17→```bash\n    18→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const m = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); console.log(Object.keys(m).filter(k => ['validateRuntime','checkBackendHealth','queryTelemetryEvents','mapEventsToModules'].includes(k)))\"\n    19→```\n    20→\n    21→```output\n    22→[\n    23→  'checkBackendHealth',\n    24→  'mapEventsToModules',\n    25→  'queryTelemetryEvents',\n    26→  'validateRuntime'\n    27→]\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Confirm backend is healthy:\n    31→\n    32→```bash\n    33→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); obs.checkBackendHealth('http://localhost:9428').then(h => console.log('healthy:', h))\"\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→```output\n    37→healthy: true\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→Set up a test project and run validateRuntime with the real observability backend:\n    41→\n    42→```bash\n    43→docker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/test-ac1/src/modules/core && echo \"// core\" > /tmp/test-ac1/src/modules/core/index.ts && echo \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"test\\\",\\\"scripts\\\":{\\\"test\\\":\\\"echo ok\\\"}}\" > /tmp/test-ac1/package.json'\n    44→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\n    45→const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\n    46→obs.validateRuntime('/tmp/test-ac1', {\n    47→  queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:9428',\n    48→  otlpEndpoint: 'http://localhost:4318',\n    49→  testCommand: 'echo test-passed',\n    50→  timeoutMs: 30000\n    51→}).then(r => console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2)));\n    52→\"\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→```output\n    56→{\n    57→  \"success\": false,\n    58→  \"error\": \"VictoriaLogs returned 400\"\n    59→}\n    60→```\n    61→\n    62→### Root Cause\n    63→\n    64→The `queryTelemetryEvents` function constructs a VictoriaLogs query using `_stream_id:*`, which is invalid LogsQL syntax. VictoriaLogs returns HTTP 400:\n    65→\n    66→```bash\n    67→docker exec codeharness-verify curl -s 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=5m&limit=10'\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→```output\n    71→remoteAddr: \"172.18.0.1:60812\"; requestURI: /select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=5m&limit=10; cannot parse query [_stream_id:*]: cannot parse _stream_id: cannot unmarshal _stream_id from \"*\"; context: [_stream_id:*]\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→A wildcard query (`*`) works correctly:\n    75→\n    76→```bash\n    77→docker exec codeharness-verify curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=5m&limit=10'\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→```output\n    81→200\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→**Failure detail:** The health check passes, the test command executes with OTEL env var set, but the post-test telemetry query always fails with 400 due to the invalid `_stream_id:*` query syntax. The intent of AC1 (query backend for telemetry events during the test window) is implemented in the code flow, but the query itself is broken against the real VictoriaLogs backend.\n    85→\n    86→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for any user interaction during this verification session.\n    87→\n    88→---\n    89→\n    90→## AC 2: Given 8 modules in the project and 5 emitted telemetry, When reported, Then runtime coverage = 62.5% with the 3 silent modules listed\n    91→\n    92→**Verdict: PASS**\n    93→\n    94→### Evidence\n    95→\n    96→Call `mapEventsToModules` with 5 events across 8 modules (analytics, reporting, admin have no telemetry):\n    97→\n    98→```bash\n    99→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\n   100→const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\n   101→const modules = ['auth', 'billing', 'notifications', 'search', 'coverage', 'analytics', 'reporting', 'admin'];\n   102→const events = [\n   103→  { source: 'src/modules/auth/login.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:00Z', attributes: {} },\n   104→  { source: 'src/modules/billing/charge.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:01Z', attributes: {} },\n   105→  { source: 'src/modules/notifications/email.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:02Z', attributes: {} },\n   106→  { source: 'src/modules/search/query.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:03Z', attributes: {} },\n   107→  { source: 'src/modules/coverage/scan.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:04Z', attributes: {} },\n   108→];\n   109→const result = obs.mapEventsToModules(events, '/tmp/test', modules);\n   110→const withTelemetry = result.filter(e => e.telemetryDetected).length;\n   111→const silent = result.filter(e => !e.telemetryDetected).map(e => e.moduleName);\n   112→console.log('Entries:', JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n   113→console.log('Coverage:', (withTelemetry / modules.length * 100) + '%');\n   114→console.log('Silent modules:', JSON.stringify(silent));\n   115→\"\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→```output\n   119→Entries: [\n   120→  { \"moduleName\": \"auth\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n   121→  { \"moduleName\": \"billing\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n   122→  { \"moduleName\": \"notifications\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n   123→  { \"moduleName\": \"search\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n   124→  { \"moduleName\": \"coverage\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n   125→  { \"moduleName\": \"analytics\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 },\n   126→  { \"moduleName\": \"reporting\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 },\n   127→  { \"moduleName\": \"admin\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 }\n   128→]\n   129→Coverage: 62.5%\n   130→Silent modules: [\"analytics\",\"reporting\",\"admin\"]\n   131→```\n   132→\n   133→**Result:** 5/8 modules with telemetry = 62.5% coverage. Silent modules (analytics, reporting, admin) correctly identified and listed.\n   134→\n   135→---\n   136→\n   137→## AC 3: Given the observability stack is not running, When the runtime check runs, Then it reports \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\" as a warning, not a hard failure\n   138→\n   139→**Verdict: PASS**\n   140→\n   141→### Evidence\n   142→\n   143→Call `validateRuntime` with a queryEndpoint pointing to an unreachable host:\n   144→\n   145→```bash\n   146→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\n   147→const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\n   148→obs.validateRuntime('/tmp/test-ac3', {\n   149→  queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999',\n   150→  testCommand: 'echo test',\n   151→  otlpEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999'\n   152→}).then(r => console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2)));\n   153→\"\n   154→```\n   155→\n   156→```output\n   157→{\n   158→  \"success\": true,\n   159→  \"data\": {\n   160→    \"entries\": [],\n   161→    \"totalModules\": 0,\n   162→    \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 0,\n   163→    \"coveragePercent\": 0,\n   164→    \"skipped\": true,\n   165→    \"skipReason\": \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n   166→  }\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→Confirm the health check returns false for unreachable endpoint:\n   171→\n   172→```bash\n   173→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); obs.checkBackendHealth('http://localhost:99999').then(h => console.log('healthy:', h))\"\n   174→```\n   175→\n   176→```output\n   177→healthy: false\n   178→```\n   179→\n   180→**Result:** When the backend is unreachable, `validateRuntime` returns `success: true` (not a hard failure) with `skipped: true` and the exact expected skip reason: `\"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"`.\n   181→\n   182→---\n   183→\n   184→## Summary\n   185→\n   186→| AC | Description | Verdict |\n   187→|----|-------------|---------|\n   188→| 1  | Observability backend queried for telemetry events during test window | **FAIL** — `queryTelemetryEvents` uses invalid LogsQL syntax (`_stream_id:*`) causing 400 from VictoriaLogs |\n   189→| 2  | Runtime coverage = 62.5% with 3 silent modules listed | **PASS** |\n   190→| 3  | Graceful skip when observability stack not running | **PASS** |\n   191→\n   192→### Bug Detail for AC1\n   193→\n   194→The `queryTelemetryEvents` function hardcodes the query `_stream_id:*` which is not valid VictoriaLogs LogsQL syntax. The `_stream_id` field cannot be queried with a wildcard `*`. A valid alternative would be the wildcard query `*` which matches all log entries. The health check, test execution with OTEL env var, and post-test query flow are all correctly orchestrated — only the query string itself is broken.\n   195→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea9dcd26-048d-426f-9aa1-49ae9968ed9a","uuid":"51562a0d-3ef7-49a4-90eb-0bc802f93a74","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:56:41.543Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode-proof.md","content":"# Story 2.3: Standalone Runtime Check (Audit Mode) — Verification Proof\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-20\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n**Container:** codeharness-verify\n\n---\n\n## AC 1: Given codeharness audit runs, When OTLP is enabled and tests run, Then the observability backend is queried for telemetry events during the test window\n\n**Verdict: FAIL**\n\n### Evidence\n\nFirst, confirm the 4 exported functions exist:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const m = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); console.log(Object.keys(m).filter(k => ['validateRuntime','checkBackendHealth','queryTelemetryEvents','mapEventsToModules'].includes(k)))\"\n```\n\n```output\n[\n  'checkBackendHealth',\n  'mapEventsToModules',\n  'queryTelemetryEvents',\n  'validateRuntime'\n]\n```\n\nConfirm backend is healthy:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); obs.checkBackendHealth('http://localhost:9428').then(h => console.log('healthy:', h))\"\n```\n\n```output\nhealthy: true\n```\n\nSet up a test project and run validateRuntime with the real observability backend:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/test-ac1/src/modules/core && echo \"// core\" > /tmp/test-ac1/src/modules/core/index.ts && echo \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"test\\\",\\\"scripts\\\":{\\\"test\\\":\\\"echo ok\\\"}}\" > /tmp/test-ac1/package.json'\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\nconst obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\nobs.validateRuntime('/tmp/test-ac1', {\n  queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:9428',\n  otlpEndpoint: 'http://localhost:4318',\n  testCommand: 'echo test-passed',\n  timeoutMs: 30000\n}).then(r => console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2)));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": \"VictoriaLogs returned 400\"\n}\n```\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe `queryTelemetryEvents` function constructs a VictoriaLogs query using `_stream_id:*`, which is invalid LogsQL syntax. VictoriaLogs returns HTTP 400:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify curl -s 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=5m&limit=10'\n```\n\n```output\nremoteAddr: \"172.18.0.1:60812\"; requestURI: /select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=5m&limit=10; cannot parse query [_stream_id:*]: cannot parse _stream_id: cannot unmarshal _stream_id from \"*\"; context: [_stream_id:*]\n```\n\nA wildcard query (`*`) works correctly:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=5m&limit=10'\n```\n\n```output\n200\n```\n\n**Failure detail:** The health check passes, the test command executes with OTEL env var set, but the post-test telemetry query always fails with 400 due to the invalid `_stream_id:*` query syntax. The intent of AC1 (query backend for telemetry events during the test window) is implemented in the code flow, but the query itself is broken against the real VictoriaLogs backend.\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for any user interaction during this verification session.\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: Given 8 modules in the project and 5 emitted telemetry, When reported, Then runtime coverage = 62.5% with the 3 silent modules listed\n\n**Verdict: PASS**\n\n### Evidence\n\nCall `mapEventsToModules` with 5 events across 8 modules (analytics, reporting, admin have no telemetry):\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\nconst obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\nconst modules = ['auth', 'billing', 'notifications', 'search', 'coverage', 'analytics', 'reporting', 'admin'];\nconst events = [\n  { source: 'src/modules/auth/login.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:00Z', attributes: {} },\n  { source: 'src/modules/billing/charge.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:01Z', attributes: {} },\n  { source: 'src/modules/notifications/email.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:02Z', attributes: {} },\n  { source: 'src/modules/search/query.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:03Z', attributes: {} },\n  { source: 'src/modules/coverage/scan.ts', message: '', timestamp: '2026-03-20T00:00:04Z', attributes: {} },\n];\nconst result = obs.mapEventsToModules(events, '/tmp/test', modules);\nconst withTelemetry = result.filter(e => e.telemetryDetected).length;\nconst silent = result.filter(e => !e.telemetryDetected).map(e => e.moduleName);\nconsole.log('Entries:', JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\nconsole.log('Coverage:', (withTelemetry / modules.length * 100) + '%');\nconsole.log('Silent modules:', JSON.stringify(silent));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\nEntries: [\n  { \"moduleName\": \"auth\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"billing\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"notifications\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"search\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"coverage\", \"telemetryDetected\": true, \"eventCount\": 1 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"analytics\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"reporting\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 },\n  { \"moduleName\": \"admin\", \"telemetryDetected\": false, \"eventCount\": 0 }\n]\nCoverage: 62.5%\nSilent modules: [\"analytics\",\"reporting\",\"admin\"]\n```\n\n**Result:** 5/8 modules with telemetry = 62.5% coverage. Silent modules (analytics, reporting, admin) correctly identified and listed.\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: Given the observability stack is not running, When the runtime check runs, Then it reports \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\" as a warning, not a hard failure\n\n**Verdict: PASS**\n\n### Evidence\n\nCall `validateRuntime` with a queryEndpoint pointing to an unreachable host:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"\nconst obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js');\nobs.validateRuntime('/tmp/test-ac3', {\n  queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999',\n  testCommand: 'echo test',\n  otlpEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999'\n}).then(r => console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2)));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"entries\": [],\n    \"totalModules\": 0,\n    \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 0,\n    \"coveragePercent\": 0,\n    \"skipped\": true,\n    \"skipReason\": \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nConfirm the health check returns false for unreachable endpoint:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const obs = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js'); obs.checkBackendHealth('http://localhost:99999').then(h => console.log('healthy:', h))\"\n```\n\n```output\nhealthy: false\n```\n\n**Result:** When the backend is unreachable, `validateRuntime` returns `success: true` (not a hard failure) with `skipped: true` and the exact expected skip reason: `\"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Verdict |\n|----|-------------|---------|\n| 1  | Observability backend queried for telemetry events during test window | **FAIL** — `queryTelemetryEvents` uses invalid LogsQL syntax (`_stream_id:*`) causing 400 from VictoriaLogs |\n| 2  | Runtime coverage = 62.5% with 3 silent modules listed | **PASS** |\n| 3  | Graceful skip when observability stack not running | **PASS** |\n\n### Bug Detail for AC1\n\nThe `queryTelemetryEvents` function hardcodes the query `_stream_id:*` which is not valid VictoriaLogs LogsQL syntax. The `_stream_id` field cannot be queried with a wildcard `*`. A valid alternative would be the wildcard query `*` which matches all log entries. The health check, test execution with OTEL env var, and post-test query flow are all correctly orchestrated — only the query string itself is broken.\n","numLines":195,"startLine":1,"totalLines":195}}}
