{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011Yagm9p8dBUVtkc9YNH8c4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RVfduNYtKfKtqtM7feAS6R","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"You are a black-box verifier re-verifying a story after a bug fix. AC2 and AC3 already passed. Focus on AC1 which previously FAILED because queryTelemetryEvents used invalid LogsQL syntax (_stream_id:*). The fix changed it to just *.\n\n## Story: 2.3 Standalone Runtime Check (Audit Mode)\n\n### ACs to verify:\n1. Given codeharness audit runs, When OTLP is enabled and tests run, Then the observability backend is queried for telemetry events during the test window.\n2. Given 8 modules in the project and 5 emitted telemetry, When reported, Then runtime coverage = 62.5% with the 3 silent modules listed.\n3. Given the observability stack is not running, When the runtime check runs, Then it reports 'runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available' as a warning, not a hard failure.\n\n### Context:\n- This story implements a MODULE-LEVEL FUNCTION (validateRuntime), NOT a CLI command\n- The observability module is at /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js\n- Exports: validateRuntime, checkBackendHealth, queryTelemetryEvents, mapEventsToModules\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL commands via: docker exec codeharness-verify <cmd>\n- VictoriaLogs at http://localhost:9428\n\n### Instructions:\n1. Verify ALL 3 ACs (not just AC1) — we need a complete proof\n2. For AC1: Create a temp project dir, call validateRuntime with real backend endpoints. Confirm it returns success (not the old 400 error). The test command can be something simple like 'echo ok'.\n3. For AC2: Call mapEventsToModules with 8 modules and 5 events matching 5 of them. Verify coverage = 62.5% and silent modules listed.\n4. For AC3: Call validateRuntime with unreachable endpoint. Confirm skipped result with exact message.\n\n### Observability Check:\nAfter each docker exec command, query: curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-30s&limit=100'\nIf zero events: [OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n### Write Proof:\nWrite to: verification/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode-proof.md\n\nUse format:\n## AC N: description\nVerdict: PASS or FAIL\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nIMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages. Report REAL failures. Do NOT fabricate evidence.\" 2>&1","description":"Re-run verifier for AC1 fix","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":352,"cache_read_input_tokens":67531,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":352},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea9dcd26-048d-426f-9aa1-49ae9968ed9a","uuid":"c5e4af84-a9a1-4944-8463-071767284306"}
